---
/**
 * /leaderboard — 301 Redirect (non-authoritative cache page retired)
 *
 * The legacy /leaderboard SSR page read the RETIRED static
 * /cache/benchmarks.json(.gz) path, masked fetch failure as a loading
 * placeholder, and fabricated freshness from the current timestamp —
 * split-truth + non-authoritative cache + fake freshness. It was retired
 * under the Surface Integrity phase (P-02/P-03).
 *
 * In this output:'server' + Cloudflare deployment the SSR worker intercepts
 * all routes, so public/_redirects FILE rules do NOT fire — only an SSR
 * redirect page actually redirects. This page is that redirect: a permanent
 * 301 to /benchmarks (the VFS-backed authoritative catalog). No data fetch,
 * no cache read, no freshness fabrication, no leaderboard UI.
 */
return Astro.redirect('/benchmarks', 301);
---
